tourBios.intlVics: (2): 2005 Mitsubishi Diamond Cup Golf [Jpn]. 2012 The Crowns [Jpn].
tourBios.carHigh:
Played on the Korean Golf Tour since 1998 and has four wins on that Tour. 

2013: Made the cut in four of nine Web.com Tour starts, with a pair of top-25 weeks...Birdied six of his final 10 holes for a final-round 66 and a T6 finish at the Chile Classic, his second career Tour start...A solid week in the hills near Pittsburgh netted him a T3 finish at the Mylan Classic in early August and into contention for the Web.com Tour Finals at No. 76...Missed cuts in his last two starts in Knoxville and Omaha shoved him to 88th at the end of the Regular Season. 

2012: Won The Crowns on the Japan Golf Tour for his second career title on that Tour. Shot back-to-back 66s on the weekend to defeat Steven Conran and Yoshikazu Haku by two strokes...Added a sixth-place showing in Japan in August at the Vana H Cup KBC Augusta...Had back-to-back T7s in October, at the Canon Open and the Japan Open...Final top-10 of the campaiagn was a fifth-place showing at the Mynavi ABC Championship. 2005: Won the Mitsubishi Diamond Cup Golf on the Japan Golf Tour.
tourBios.personal: His father owned a driving range growing up...Entrance song on the first tee would be "Gangnam Style."...Is a big Los Angeles Lakers fan...Favorite book is Zen Golf, Mastering the Mental Game...Would love to trade places with Fred Couples because he loves his swing.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Web.com Tour was T3rd in 2013 at the Mylan Classic.
